# Test Plan

## Scope:
- Authentication
  - Registration
  - Login
  - Password Recovery
- Catalog
- Community

## Test Types:
- Manual functional testing
- Exploratory testing
- Positive and negative testing
- Validation testing
- UI/UX testing

## Test Approach:
- Testing was performed based on requirements analysis and exploratory testing.
- Bugs were reported in Jira with detailed steps to reproduce, expected and actual results.

## Test Data:
- Valid and invalid emails
- Emails with special characters and Cyrillic symbols
- Passwords with different length and symbols
- Rapid user actions (Multiple clicks)

## Test Environment:
- Web application: https://demowebshop.tricentis.com/
- Browser: Microsoft Edge
- OS: Windows 11

## Found Issues:
- Validation issues (email format, password rules)
- UI/UX issues (action buttons are not disabled after submission, overlapping elements)
- Logical issues (multiple form submissions)
- Session handling issues (Session persistence)

## Results:
- Total bugs found: 21
- Total test-cases written: 60

## Potential risks:
- Duplicate form submissions may lead to backend issues
- Weak validation can cause problems with user data integrity  

